THE SATURDAYS stripped down to tiny corsets and sequin skirts to open their Greatest Hits tour in Glasgow. The Saturdays Glasgow - Daily Record 
The gorgeous girl group celebrated six years of hits in Glasgow.
The five-piece stripped down to tiny gold skirts and low-cut bra tops for the opening night.
And just as the singers took to the stage Frankie Bridge was also making her debut on Strictly Come Dancing.
The new mum is back to her pre-baby weight and showed off her impressive abs and toned legs in the skimpy outfit.
The girls are following up yesterday's incredible gig with another 19 nights this summer.
Check out opening night in our gallery above.
Rochelle Humes previously revealed why so many of The Saturdays' tours start in Glasgow - the shopping.
 